Dia. 01 Correct Answer
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Did you find White 1?
\par It looks a bit strange, but this is the \cf1\b only move\cf0\b0  \cf2\b which captures Black\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par If the outside liberties are filled up, White plays dansu at A or B. So Black has to take the five stones. After that White can capture Black with the placement at the center of the five space shape.
\par
\par It means this shape is already captured after White plays at 1.
\par
\par }
