Dia. 02 Dead Again?
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White can easily think that even if he fills the liberty from the outside with 1, he can still capture Black.
\par
\par If Black plays at 2, White answers with 3 and it becomes a famous dead shape.
\par
\par However is this sequence correct? Actually not. Black 2 is \cf1\b questionable\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par }
